data.title: Australia Day Honours 2021: Ken Fitch, Mark Randolph and Chrissie Parrott recognised for service to WA
data.meta_description: Perth doctor Ken Fitch, engineering professor Mark Randolph and veteran choreographer Chrissie Parrott have been recognised for their contribution to WA in the 2021 Australia Day Honours list.
data.text:
Perth doctor Ken Fitch is a pioneer of sports medicine in Australia, who helped to develop the anti-doping codes used today in global sport.

The 88-year-old has attended 18 Olympic Games, working for the Australian Olympic Committee (AOC) and more recently the International Olympic Committee (IOC).
